This paper deals with information theory and coding theory, specifically the capacity and error exponents of the AWGN channel and the modulo-lattice channel. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves number theory and modular arithmetic, which suggests cs.NT (Number Theory) as a possible sub-category. The use of geometric concepts and codes points towards cs.SI (Signal Processing) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper involves mathematical analysis and proofs, which could fall under cs.DS (Discrete Mathematics and Combinatorics).
